''Refrain''<br>
Kuwait, my country, may you be safe and glorious!<br>
May you always enjoy good fortune!<br>
You are the cradle of my ancestors,<br>
Who put down its memory.

''First stanza''<br>
With everlasting symmetry, showing all eternity,<br>
Those Arabs were heavenly,<br>
Kuwait, my country,<br>
May you be safe and glorious!<br>
May you always enjoy good fortune.

''Second stanza''<br>
Blessed be my Country a homeland for harmony,<br>
Warded by true sentry giving their soils aptly,<br>
Building high its history, Kuwait,<br>
My country, we're for you my Country,

''Third stanza''<br>
Led by faith and loyalty,<br>
With its Amir equally,<br>
Fencing us all fairly, with warm love and verity,<br>

Kuwait, my country,
May you be safe and glorious.<br>
May you always enjoy good fortune!<br>
